Cooldown_Unit_Concrete_Test
└── When updating the cooldown settings // Cooldown limits can be enabled, disabled, or modified.
    └── When a non-owner tries to update cooldown settings
        └── It should revert.
            └── Because only the contract owner can update cooldown settings.
            └── And it should revert with OwnableUnauthorizedAccount.
    └── When setting cooldown blocks to zero
        └── It should revert.
            └── Because cooldown blocks must be greater than zero.
            └── And it should revert with InvalidCooldown.
    └── When setting a valid cooldown block duration
        └── It should update the `cooldownBlocks` state variable.
            └── Because the contract should enforce the new cooldown duration.
        └── It should emit a `CooldownBlocksUpdated` event.
            └── Because logs should track changes to cooldown settings.
    └── When enabling cooldowns
        └── It should update `isCooldownEnabled` to true.
            └── Because cooldowns should no longer be enforced.
        └── It should emit a `CooldownEnabledUpdated` event.
            └── Because logs should track cooldown deactivation.
    └── When disabling cooldowns
        └── It should update `isCooldownEnabled` to false.
            └── Because cooldowns should no longer be enforced.
        └── It should emit a `CooldownEnabledUpdated` event.
            └── Because logs should track cooldown deactivation.
